HEADWORD: Spheromere
<hw>Sphe"ro*mere</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sphere</ets> + <ets>-mere</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of the several symmetrical segments arranged around the
central axis and composing the body of a radiate animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

